BIG&nbsp;WEEK&nbsp;AT&nbsp;BIG&nbsp;SUR&nbsp;/&nbsp;13<br>
&quot;known&quot;&nbsp;about&nbsp;the&nbsp;structure&nbsp;of&nbsp;atoms&nbsp;He&nbsp;started&nbsp;with&nbsp;what<br>he&nbsp;really<i>&nbsp;knew</i>&nbsp;about&nbsp;atoms,&nbsp;that&nbsp;is,&nbsp;he&nbsp;started&nbsp;with&nbsp;raw<br>spectroscopic&nbsp;data&nbsp;Bohr&nbsp;speculated&nbsp;that&nbsp;electrons&nbsp;revolve<br>
around&nbsp;the&nbsp;nucleus&nbsp;of&nbsp;an&nbsp;atom&nbsp;not&nbsp;at&nbsp;just&nbsp;any&nbsp;distance,&nbsp;but&nbsp;in<br>orbits&nbsp;or&nbsp;shells,&nbsp;which&nbsp;are&nbsp;specific&nbsp;distances&nbsp;from&nbsp;the&nbsp;nucleus<br>
Each&nbsp;of&nbsp;these&nbsp;shells<br>
