thority&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;day,&nbsp;which&nbsp;was&nbsp;Aristotle&nbsp;According&nbsp;to&nbsp;Aristotle,<br>the&nbsp;natural&nbsp;inclination&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;moving&nbsp;object&nbsp;is&nbsp;to&nbsp;return&nbsp;to&nbsp;a<br>state&nbsp;of&nbsp;rest<br>
