Nonetheless,&nbsp;where&nbsp;the&nbsp;conservation&nbsp;laws&nbsp;have&nbsp;jurisdiction,<br>
they&nbsp;are&nbsp;inviolable&nbsp;rules&nbsp;which&nbsp;shape&nbsp;the&nbsp;form&nbsp;of&nbsp;all&nbsp;particle<br>interactions&nbsp;For&nbsp;example,&nbsp;the&nbsp;conservation&nbsp;law&nbsp;of&nbsp;mass-energy<br>dictates&nbsp;that&nbsp;all&nbsp;spontaneous&nbsp;particle&nbsp;decays&nbsp;be&nbsp;'&nbsp;downhill&nbsp;&quot;<br>When&nbsp;a&nbsp;single&nbsp;particle<br>
&nbsp;decays,&nbsp;it&nbsp;always&nbsp;decays<br>
