<A name=265></a><IMG src="dancingmasters-265_1.png"><br>
THE&nbsp;DANCE&nbsp;/&nbsp;249<br>
According&nbsp;to&nbsp;S-Matrix&nbsp;theory,&nbsp;&quot;particles'&nbsp;are<i>&nbsp;intermediate</i><br>
<i>states</i>&nbsp;in&nbsp;a&nbsp;network&nbsp;of&nbsp;interactions.&nbsp;The&nbsp;lines&nbsp;in&nbsp;an&nbsp;S-Matrix<br>diagram&nbsp;are&nbsp;not&nbsp;the&nbsp;world&nbsp;lines&nbsp;of&nbsp;different&nbsp;particles.&nbsp;Lines&nbsp;in<br>
an&nbsp;S-Matrix&nbsp;diagram&nbsp;of&nbsp;an&nbsp;interaction&nbsp;network&nbsp;are&nbsp;&quot;reaction<br>channels&quot;&nbsp;through&nbsp;which&nbsp;energy&nbsp;flows.&nbsp;A&nbsp;&quot;neutron,&quot;&nbsp;for<br>example,&nbsp;is&nbsp;a<i>&nbsp;reaction&nbsp;channel.</i>&nbsp;It&nbsp;can&nbsp;be&nbsp;formed&nbsp;by&nbsp;a&nbsp;proton<br>and&nbsp;a&nbsp;negative&nbsp;pion.<br>
