&nbsp;spin&nbsp;is&nbsp;at&nbsp;the<br>
center.&nbsp;One&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;particles&nbsp;goes&nbsp;to&nbsp;area&nbsp;A.&nbsp;In&nbsp;area&nbsp;A&nbsp;it&nbsp;goes<br>through&nbsp;a&nbsp;Stern-Gerlach&nbsp;device.&nbsp;In&nbsp;this&nbsp;case,&nbsp;the&nbsp;Stern-<br>Gerlach&nbsp;device&nbsp;gives&nbsp;it&nbsp;a&nbsp;spin<i>&nbsp;up.</i>&nbsp;Therefore,&nbsp;we&nbsp;know<i>&nbsp;without</i><br>
